Electric and Gas Choice 
Communication Bulletin # 65

                                             _________________________September 14, 2001



STAKEHOLDER:  Suppliers Receiving this bulletin.  

SUBJECT:  January-April 2001 Energy Reconciliation Calculation Error and Necessary Credit/Charge adjustment. 

PURPOSE of COMMUNICATION: 
To inform Electric Generation Suppliers (EGS) of an error in the calculation of Unaccounted-For-Energy (UFE) for the months January 2001 through April 2001 and necessary additional cash settlement between the EGS and PECO. 

KEY FACTS:
Electric & Gas Choice Group (E&GC) has recently completed an extensive analysis of PJM Energy Reconciliation amounts for the periods of January 2001-April 2001.
As a result of that analysis E&GC has determined some modifications to monthly energy reconciliation amounts are required for those periods. 

 				 
ACTION NEEDED:
?	If you are the recipient of this email, our records show that you are impacted by these required modifications.
?	       No EGS action is needed at this time. 
?	You will be contacted shortly by an E&GC representative to discuss these required changes to the monthly energy reconciliation amounts for the aforementioned period and any necessary credit/charge adjustments. 


ANY QUESTIONS PLEASE CONTACT: The Supplier Hotline -(215) 841-3700






